{
  "texts": [
    "Sequential use of Bayes Theorem gives π t (θ|y 0:t) ∝ π t-1 (θ|y 0:t-1)p (θ) t (y t |y 0:t-1)",
    "(5) which is complicated by the observed-data likelihood p (θ)",
    "t (y t |y 0:t-1), which is typically unavailable in closed form.",
    "Given a weighted sample of size M, {θ 1:M, u 1:M t-1 }, from π t-1 (θ|y 0:t-1), an idealised SMC scheme generates a weighted sample distributed according to (5) by reweighting each θ i according to",
    "t (y t |y 0:t-1)."
  ]
}